The paper deals with the problem of detecting the support of a sparse vector from noisy measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of a specific algorithm (SequOMP) and analyzes its behavior, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses mathematical analysis and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the effect of dynamic range on thresholding performance, which is related to cs.SI (Systems and Control).
